    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Trim, then finely slice your<strong> spring onions</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-hoisin-meat-free-meatballs-with-sesame-veg-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> meat free mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to a large mixing bowl with the <strong>grated garlic</strong>, 1/3 of the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated ginger</strong> (save the rest for later!) and mix thoroughly until combined (clean hands are the best way!)</p><p>Divide the <strong>meat free mince mixture </strong>equally and shape into 3 meatballs per person</p><p>Add the<strong> meat free mince meatballs </strong>to a lightly oiled baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 14-15 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-hoisin-meat-free-meatballs-with-sesame-veg-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the meat free mince meatballs are in the oven, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-hoisin-meat-free-meatballs-with-sesame-veg-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, slice 1/4 of your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> thinly so that you are left with chilli rounds (save these for garnish!)</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Top, tail and peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-hoisin-meat-free-meatballs-with-sesame-veg-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a<strong> </strong>small splash of<strong> water</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and stir to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>hoisin</strong> <strong>sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-hoisin-meat-free-meatballs-with-sesame-veg-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1 min or until beginning to wilt</p><p>Once wilted, remove the pan from the heat and add your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> carrot ribbons </strong>and <strong>remaining sliced spring onion </strong>to the pan \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-hoisin-meat-free-meatballs-with-sesame-veg-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the<strong> sesame</strong> <strong>veg</strong> to a plate and cover to keep warm</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Remove the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>meat free mince meatballs</strong> from the oven and add them to the pan with the<strong> spiced hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min, coating the meat free mince meatballs in the sauce until thickened and becoming sticky \u2013 these are your<strong> spiced hoisin meat free meatballs</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-hoisin-meat-free-meatballs-with-sesame-veg-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>hoisin meat free meatballs</strong> with the <strong>sesame veg</strong> and <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Spoon over the <strong>spiced hoisin sauce</strong> from the pan and garnish with your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
